  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Despite the effectiveness of beta-blockers and antiplatelet agents for secondary prevention
      of coronary heart disease, this treatments are underused in the elderly because of diagnosis
      uncertainty and underuse of efficient treatment.

      in a first time, diagnosis reassessment with invasive technique if necessary. in a second
      time, treatment reassessment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
